After clicking on an NPC card on the dashboard, the NPC should center itself and the dashboard should switch to the map.

It is necessary to optimize the sending of data between the client and the kernel.

Each tick saves a snapshot of changes to the world in storage.

The client needs to request full information about the world state upon initialization, and then request a list of snapshots of changes from the last one received to the current one.

Limit the weight and capacity that NPCs can carry to encourage the use of chests.

The chest is equipped with a simple lock when created, but it can be upgraded.

If an NPC wants to protect his things, he can put them in his chest, which has a large volume and is not limited by the weight of its capacity.

Any object that can be installed in the world, be it a house, a door, a chest, or a workbench, should have the ability to install a lock.

locks come in varying complexity.have two characteristics: brute force resistance and pick resistance. the simplest one can be made from boards

In the distant future, we need to make water streams.
